{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "easyvtc-admin-managers-collection",
    "name": "EasyVTC — Module Admin (Gestionnaires & Dashboard)",
    "description": "# EasyVTC — Module Admin complet\n\n## Setup\n1. Importer cette collection **et** l'environnement `EasyVTC_Local`\n2. Vérifier que `admin_email` / `admin_password` sont renseignés dans l'environnement\n3. Lancer l'API : `npm run dev`\n4. Exécuter **🔐 Authentification** en premier\n5. Suivre les dossiers dans l'ordre numéroté\n\n## Variables sauvegardées automatiquement\n- `admin_token` — après le login admin\n- `manager_id` — après `POST /admin/managers`\n- `target_user_id` — après la liste des users (premier résultat non-admin)\n- `reservation_id` — à renseigner manuellement (UUID d'une réservation en statut `pending`)\n- `driver_record_id` — à renseigner manuellement (UUID de la table `public.drivers`)\n\n## Routes couvertes\n```\nPOST  /admin/managers\nGET   /admin/users\nGET   /admin/users/:id\nPUT   /admin/users/:id/status\nGET   /admin/reservations\nGET   /admin/reservations/:id\nPUT   /admin/reservations/:id/assign\nGET   /admin/stats\n```\n\n## Rôles\n- Routes `/admin/users`, `/admin/managers`, `/admin/stats` : **admin uniquement**\n- Routes `/admin/reservations` : **admin + manager**",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",        "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",     "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "manager_id",      "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Sauvegardé après POST /admin/managers" },
    { "key": "target_user_id",  "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Sauvegardé après GET /admin/users (premier résultat)" },
    { "key": "reservation_id",  "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "UUID d'une réservation en statut pending — à renseigner manuellement" },
    { "key": "driver_record_id","value": "", "type": "string", "description": "UUID de public.drivers (pas users.id) — à renseigner manuellement" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Authentification",
      "description": "Exécuter en premier pour peupler admin_token.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth","login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{admin_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{admin_password}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('admin_token sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(json.data.user.role).to.equal('admin');",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', json.data.access_token);",
            "  console.log(' admin_token sauvegardé');",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login Admin — Mauvais mot de passe (401)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth","login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{admin_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"mauvais\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
            "pm.test('ok: false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "1️⃣ Créer un gestionnaire",
      "description": "POST /admin/managers — Crée un compte manager, génère un mot de passe temporaire et envoie l'email.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Créer un gestionnaire ",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/managers", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","managers"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"first_name\": \"Sophie\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Martin\",\n  \"email\": \"manager.test@easyvtc.fr\",\n  \"phone\": \"+33612345678\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
            "pm.test('ok: true + rôle manager + manager_id sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(json.data.role).to.equal('manager');",
            "  pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('id');",
            "  pm.expect(json.data).to.not.have.property('temp_password');",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('manager_id', json.data.id);",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('target_user_id', json.data.id);",
            "  console.log(' manager_id sauvegardé:', json.data.id);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Créer gestionnaire — email manquant (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/managers", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","managers"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"first_name\": \"Sophie\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Martin\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 — Zod email manquant', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
            "pm.test('erreur sur champ email', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.false;",
            "  pm.expect(json.errors).to.have.property('email');",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Créer gestionnaire — prénom trop court (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/managers", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","managers"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"first_name\": \"A\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Martin\",\n  \"email\": \"mgr2@easyvtc.fr\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 — prénom trop court', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
            "pm.test('erreur sur first_name', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.false;",
            "  pm.expect(json.errors).to.have.property('first_name');",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Créer gestionnaire — email déjà utilisé (409)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/managers", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","managers"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"first_name\": \"Sophie\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Martin\",\n  \"email\": \"manager.test@easyvtc.fr\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 409 — email dupliqué', () => pm.response.to.have.status(409));",
            "pm.test('ok: false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Non authentifié] Créer gestionnaire — token absent (401)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/managers", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","managers"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"first_name\": \"Test\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Anon\",\n  \"email\": \"anon@test.com\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 401 — non authentifié', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
            "pm.test('ok: false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "2️⃣ Lister les utilisateurs",
      "description": "GET /admin/users — Liste paginée de tous les utilisateurs, filtrable par rôle, statut, recherche.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Liste tous les utilisateurs ",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/users",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","users"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('ok: true + liste paginée', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(json.data.users).to.be.an('array');",
            "  pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('total');",
            "  pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('total_pages');",
            "  if (json.data.users.length > 0) {",
            "    const nonAdmin = json.data.users.find(u => u.role !== 'admin');",
            "    if (nonAdmin) {",
            "      pm.collectionVariables.set('target_user_id', nonAdmin.id);",
            "      console.log(' target_user_id sauvegardé:', nonAdmin.id);",
            "    }",
            "  }",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Liste — filtrer par rôle manager",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/users?role=manager",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","users"],
              "query": [{ "key": "role", "value": "manager" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('tous les résultats ont rôle manager', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
            "  json.data.users.forEach(u => pm.expect(u.role).to.equal('manager'));",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Liste — filtrer par statut active",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/users?status=active",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","users"],
              "query": [{ "key": "status", "value": "active" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('ok: true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.true);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Liste — recherche par email",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/users?search=easyvtc",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","users"],
              "query": [{ "key": "search", "value": "easyvtc" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('ok: true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.true);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Liste — pagination page 2, limit 5",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/users?page=2&limit=5",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","users"],
              "query": [{ "key": "page", "value": "2" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "5" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('page=2 retournée', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(json.data.page).to.equal(2);",
            "  pm.expect(json.data.limit).to.equal(5);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Liste — limit invalide (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/users?limit=500",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","users"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "500" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 — limit > 100', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
            "pm.test('ok: false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Non-admin] Liste — accès refusé (403)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/users", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","users"] }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 403', () => pm.response.to.have.status(403));",
            "pm.test('ok: false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "3️⃣ Consulter un utilisateur",
      "description": "GET /admin/users/:id — Profil complet d'un utilisateur. Utilise target_user_id sauvegardé à l'étape 2.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Profil d'un utilisateur ",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/users/{{target_user_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","users","{{target_user_id}}"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('ok: true + id correspond', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(json.data.id).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('target_user_id'));",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] Profil — ID inexistant (404)",
          "request": {
